That said, this is an invite to all my friends from / in Milan to link up in these last days, at least to say hi (and maybe smoke a joint together). I wanted to take the proper time to show appreciation to you all and say goodbye (not farewell). (6)

As many of you know, I'm a T1D and stress has a big impact on my well being. I love the big city and everything it offers but at heart I'm still a country boy who need his spaces. And I can't spend the summer faraway from the beach ğŸ˜‚ (5)

After leaving my previous job my priorities became investing, connecting and building. I'm more than satisfied with the job I've been doing 'till now and the results speak for themselves. The price I payed for this was overworking myself and sacrificing my health. (4)

with all the activities we started.
When I came here first, I was a different person: A young CRA looking to climb the corp ladder. Took me a month to earn more than my previous boss thanks to NFTs, and another month to understand I wasn't cut for that 9/5 crap. (3)

I'm grateful for all the people I had the chance to meet and connect with, we'll keep in touch and I'll be visiting you soon. Everything we started building together, it's still my priority (like, if I told ya #NFTMilano2022 what would you say?) and I'm dedicated to go on (2)

gm.
Last 20ish days in Milan, before going back to my hometown to enjoy some tranquillity.
This is temporary as I'll be back next fall, I don't have any urgency to be here now and I'll be visiting on a monthly basis.
I'll take some time to focus on building and on my health. (1)
